==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/'θɪn/}}
* {{audio|en-us-thin.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|ɪn}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang}} ''[[þynne]]'', from {{proto|Germanic|þunnu}} < *þen, from {{proto|Indo-European|ten-|to stretch}}.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|thinner|thinnest}}

# Slim, [[narrow]] in size, and (''of a person or animal'') usually carrying little fat.
# Of low [[viscosity]] or low specific [[gravity]], e.g., as is water compared to honey.
# [[scarce|Scarce]].
# Overly [[strict]].
# {{sports}} Describing a poorly played [[golf]] shot where the ball is struck by the bottom part of the club head. See [[fat]], [[shank]], [[toe]].

